@node main "BareED 0.34 - a brief introduction"

@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
@{fg highlight}Please,  do  not  expect  too much from this file nor from BareED itself. BareED is currently only available as a
pre-version (beta) that suits my needs and perhaps also yours.
@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}

Although BareED is very stable on my system, it is possible that BareED will @{fg shine}@{" fail " link helpnode}@{fg highlight} on yours!@{fg text}

 - @{b}What is BareED.@{ub}
	BareED is a simple to use text editor that will use the ASCII one character set for Amiga computers.

 - @{b}Why another text editor when already hundreds are available?@{ub}
	I  originally  designed  BareED as replacement for NotePad, the first word-processor for the Amiga,
	Amiga-ED, the batch and script editor, and Amiga-MEmacs, the text editor.

	What  I  did like most about NotePad was its ability to change text and background colours and that
	NotePad  also  offered  the  possibility  to use proportional fonts. Although NotePad was much more
	powerful  than  BareED regarding text styles and fonts, it had so many limitations so that only a few
	people did use NotePad at all.

	The  use  of  Amiga-MEmacs  on  an  intuitive  driven  platform like the Amiga is a pain in the butt.

	Although   newer   versions  of  Amiga-ED  have  been  published  they  cannot  count  for  much
	comfortable nor can they be used to edit normal text files.

	My favourite text editor was the one shipped with the Devpacą package - clean and easy to use!

	BareED  is  one  of  the  few  text editors on the Amiga, who will not use the Amiga console device
	and therefore non-rigid colours and non-fixed width fonts can be used.

	BareED  also  is  one  of the few text editors that deal correctly with a sizeable editor window; even
	commercial  text  editors  have  problems with that. So you can use BareED like a notepad on your
	Workbench  -  that means that you reduce BareED's editor window to a minimum and leave it open
	anywhere  on  your  Workbench  desk  while  you  do  other  things.  When  you need BareED, for
	example  to  remember  important  stuff,  you  activate  BareED  only  (without  enlarging  the editor
	window to a maximum) and enter the letters.

	@{fg highlight}Although  BareED  is  relatively  quick  on  my  system,  it is possible that BareED is really slow on
	yours  -  due  to  the calculations that must be done before something can be performed; nothing is
	rigid in BareED!
	Therefore  it  is  quite  modest  at  consuming  memory but can slow down your machine to its limits
	while you scroll around in the text file or enter characters.@{fg text}

	BareED  has not been designed for native Amigas (like an A1200 or A4000/30) but for accelerated
	machines  with a (for Amigas) quick CPU. As if that's not bad enough, BareED should only be used
	when  a  fast  interface  to  access  system  memory is available (forget any ZIII memory expansion
	card!) and in addition - when you have installed a 3rd party graphic device.

