@node man_page "Intro, Install, Requirements, Language, Use"

BareED is a handy and easy to use text editor for your Amiga / Draco / Pegasos computer.
BareED  is  actually  only available as beta application (not completely ready yet) - but some simple files can
be edited anyhow.

It has got a different concept (as opposite to other Freeware text editors)
	Designed for non-mono-space fonts (proportional fonts).
	Does  not  use the system's console device so that the colours can be chosen for the background,
	text, cursor, and text underneath the cursor and for the marked characters.

Currently it's a really "bare" (okay, it isn't...)  but further releases may get stronger.


@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}


Installing BareED
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

(1)
To install BareED you have nothing else to do than to drag the program icon of BareED into your favourite drawer.

(2)
If  you  wish  to  store  BareED into a currently non-existing drawer select "New Drawer" from the Workbench
window menu.
Make  sure  you  are  going  to  select a suitable medium and drawer where to create the new one. If the new
directory has been created, execute step one as stated above.


To  install  the  complete  package  of  BareED  including Rexx-script, button interface, DAC port applications
and the catalogues simply drag "BareED's" drawer to your favourite position on your hard drive.
No "ASSIGN" to "BareED's" "home-directory" is needed to run BareED!


@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}


Requirements
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
BareED  can be used up from OS 3.0.

There  aren't  any specific disk resident libraries and devices used by BareED other than those your machine
was originally equipped with.


Requirements (minimum):
	Exec		v36
	Dos		v36
	Graphics	v33
	Layers		v33
	Intuition		v36
	GadTools	v36
	Diskfont		v33
	Icon		v33
	Asl		v38

	CPU 68020, 512Kb RAM, OCS

Better:
	Exec		v36
	Dos		v36
	Graphics	v39
	Layers		v39
	Intuition		v39
	GadTools	v39
	Diskfont		v33
	Icon		v33
	Asl		v39
	Locale		v38

	CPU 68030, 2MB 32-Bit RAM, AA

Perfect:
	Complete Kickstart v40 package (OS 3.1)
	68040 with onboard RAM
	3rd party graphic card plugged into Zorro 3 or Draco direct slot
	Installed Picasso96 software package
	Asl library v41/42 (Asl v40 has got several bugs...)
	Several proportional fonts either bitmap related or outlined
	Ttf (true type font engine) package by Richard Griffith


@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}


Installing a suitable catalogue (OS 2.1 (Kickstart v38))
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

To install the catalogue containing the native language strings you have first to create the catalogue:

	Edit the ".ct" file
	Use  "CatComp"  utility  (or  an  equivalent  application)  to  produce  the  "catalog"  file.  Create  a
	sub-directory on the medium where you have stored BareED called "catalogs".

	Create in this new created directory another one that is called exactly as your native language, e.g.

	 "dansk".

	 Move the translated (via "CatComp") "catalog" to this location.
	 Fully:

		"Work:Edit/Editors/BareED"		- Home-directory of BareED

		1> dir work:edit/editors/BareED
		 BareED			BareED.doc
		1> makedir work:edit/editors/BareED/catalogs
		1>
		1> makedir work:edit/editors/BareED/catalogs/dansk
		1>
		1> copy ram:BareED.catalog to work:edit/editors/BareED/catalogs/dansk
		1>
 		1> dir work:edit/editors/BareED
		 BareED			BareED.doc
		 catalogs (dir)
		1>
		1> dir work:edit/editors/BareED/catalogs
		 dansk (dir)
		1>
		1> dir work:edit/editors/BareED/catalogs/dansk
		 BareED.catalog
		1>

If  you  are  an  average  user  of  the  Amiga  OS  you might ask why to create a sub-directory in the drawer
where  BareED  stays  instead  of  using  "SYS:locale/catalogs/..../BareED.catalog". The reason why is: If you
delete  from  Workbench  the  BareED  drawer  BareED  and used by it files will also be deleted, i.e. you don't
have to scan through your system-partition to look for BareED used files, simple - eeh?


@{fg shine}_______________________________________________________________________________________@{fg shadow}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}


Usage:
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ

From  Workbench you simply double click BareED's icon. BareED then examines its icon accordingly to local
set variables (tool-types), those, which are only valid for your environment.

Launching  BareED  by  means of a shell will give you the possibility to choose not only the filename but also
the window dimension:
@{b}> BareED [filename] [window=x,y,w,h] [-keepio]@{ub}
But  please  keep  in  mind  that  even  when  BareED  was  launched  out  of a shell it nevertheless will also
examine its icon for set environment variables.

The  "@{fg highlight}-keepio@{fg text}"  switch  can  be  used in order to suppress the auto-detaching from the shell. You should use
the  switch  "@{fg highlight}-keepio@{fg text}"  in case BareED is used as an external text editor for an application which doesn't offer
the editing of a document in question.

@{fg shine}Starting with version 0.10007 of BareED the order of parameters passed in isn't anymore of importance.@{fg text}

Warning:  If  you  make  use  of  the  "@{fg highlight}-keepio@{fg text}" switch BareED runs with the stack size which was fixed by the
console  or  the  calling  programme, i.e. it may happen that BareED refuses to surface because the stack size
is less than 4000 bytes.

Because  BareED  stores  the  global  settings  in  the project-icon of the file you edited, the preferred way to
bring up BareED is to double click the project-icon!


@endnode

