Q:	Why  when I'm at start of a line, if I "shift cursor down" to scroll page, it goes to the end of line after
	the first page ?
Q:	Is  that  intentional  that the cursor goes to the end of line when I press shift+down ? (only when the
	cursor goes to end of page)

A:	It  is.  Pressing SHIFT-DOWN will ever jump to the last displayable character in the window, whilst
	SHIFT-UP will jump to the first displayable. BareED is not PageLiner nor CygnusED...

